<div class="about-me-content">
  <h1>{{ heading }}</h1>
  <p>My interests explore the intersections of seemingly disparate fields: ancient philosophy, modern technology, and the timeless nature of art. This space serves as an inquiry into the patterns that connect them.</p>

  <h2>Ancient Wisdom, Modern Questions</h2>
  <p>From the dawn of recorded history, mystic traditions have sought to answer fundamental questions about consciousness and reality. This website delves into the universal patterns found in these ancient wisdoms, comparing their insights to the challenges and perspectives of our contemporary world. It is an exploration of how timeless truths can inform our modern lives.</p>
  
  <h2>AI: A Tool for Thought</h2>
  <p>Artificial intelligence is more than just a technological marvel; it is a powerful tool for extending human creativity and analysis. Here, I examine the realistic benefits of AI as a partner in the creative process, while also acknowledging its critical limitations. True progress lies not in replacing human ingenuity, but in augmenting it, requiring careful consideration and ethical oversight.</p>

  <h2>The Digital Canvas: AI and Art</h2>
  <p>By combining a background in graphic arts and digital editing with the capabilities of AI, we can unlock new forms of expression. This website is dedicated to the practical synthesis of human artistry and machine intelligence. It is a showcase of new media created through this collaborative process, pushing the boundaries of the traditional digital canvas.</p>

